<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Yugoslav-Greens     06-12 0101</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Yugoslav-Greens,0104</SECOND>
<HEAD>Greens Form Union In Liberal Northern Republic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Environmentalists in the liberal
northern republic of Slovenia have formed a union of ecological
groups and societies, the state news agency Tanjug reported.
   The inaugural meeting of the ``Greens'' Union, held at Mostec
near the Slovenian capital of Ljubljana on Sunday, elected a
15-member executive committee, the report said.
   The union, whose guiding principle is ``Think Globally, Act
Locally,'' aims at bringing people together who share common
interests rather than ideology, the news agency said.
   Tanjug said the new organization will operate within the
Slovenian Youth Union.
</TEXT>
