<FIRST>r a AM-MayorArrested     06-12 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mayor Arrested,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mayor, Wife, 16 Others Arrested In Drug, Money-Laundering Probe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SOUTH LAKE TAHOE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The mayor of South Lake Tahoe,
his wife and 16 other people have been arrested in connection with a
20-month undercover drug and money laundering investigation,
authorities said Sunday.
   Mayor Terry Trupp and his wife, Kim, were taken into custody
Sunday on federal conspiracy and money laundering charges involving
alleged efforts to launder about $750,000 to FBI and Internal
Revenue Service agents, the bureau and other agencies announced at a
joint news conference.
   The Trupps, who are being held without bail in an El Dorado
County jail, will be arraigned Monday before a federal magistrate.
   Besides the 18 arrested in the probe, dubbed ``Deep Snow,'' two
fugitives are being sought, South Lake Tahoe police and agents of
the FBI, IRS, and Drug Enforcement Administration said.
   All are suspected of being involved in drug trafficking or
efforts to launder money from drug sales, authorities said.
   Law enforcement officials have recovered about 12 kilograms of
cocaine in arrests and seizures, agents said. No drugs were seized
in the Trupps' arrests, authorities said.
</TEXT>
