<FIRST>r w PM-KhomeiniDaughter     06-12 0213</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Khomeini Daughter,200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Daughter: Khomeini Suffered Five Heart Attacks Within Days of Cancer
Surgery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini was attended by up
to 40 doctors at a special clinic before his death, which followed
five heart attacks over a 10-day period, his daughter said in an
interview published today.
   Khomeini suffered the heart attacks following surgery for stomach
cancer May 23, said Zahra Mustafavi in an interview with The
Washington Post and Japan's Yomiuri Shimbun. Khomeini died June 3.
   The interview published in today's editions of the Post offered
the first public details of Khomeini's medical problems in the weeks
before his death.
   ``His trouble was heart attacks, which he had five times in that
10 days,'' said Mustafavi. She said that in his final days, Khomeini
was attended by as many as 40 doctors at a special clinic.
   Mustafavi said the Iranian ruler had been plagued by heart
troubles for years, suffering his first heart attack nine years ago.
His doctors took over the special clinic near his home in Tehran at
that time, she said.
   ``He almost died'' of a heart attack in 1986, Ms. Mustafavi said.
   She said Khomeini died at about 4 p.m. on June 3 after having his
last heart attack about an hour before.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
