<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--PrimalFires     06-12 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Primal Fires,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Fires Damage Primal Institute Headquarters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Investigators suspect an arsonist set fire to
the West Los Angeles offices of primal-scream psychologist Arthur
Janov only hours after firefighters extinguished another blaze there.
   Los Angeles Fire Department officials said the fires, which
caused an estimated $475,000 damage on Sunday to The Primal
Institute building, appeared to be unrelated. No one was seriously
injured.
   The first blaze broke out 12:30 a.m. and was brought under
control within a half-hour. The second was reported 6:55 a.m. and
doused shortly before 8 a.m.
   Investigators said they found traces of a flammable substance at
the scene, and Battalion Chief Chuck Merriman termed the second
blaze ``suspicious.''
   Janov is known for primal scream therapy, a treatment of mental
disorder in which the patient, often in group sessions, is induced
to re-enact infancy and to express emotions in screams and shouts.
   Officials knew of no motive for the fire. The two blazes gutted
most of Janov's therapy center, which occupies the first floor of a
two-story brick building.
