<FIRST>r i PM-Japan-USPlaneCrash     06-12 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Japan-US Plane Crash,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Military Plane Crashes into Mountain, Pilot Safe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Marine fighter plane crashed into a mountain
in southwestern Japan today, but the pilot parachuted to safety,
officials said.
   There were no reports of injuries to Japanese residents or major
damage to forests after the plane, an FA-18 Hornet jet, hit the
mountain in Ehime, on southwestern Shikoku Island, said a police
official on condition of anonymity.
   The plane, on a training flight, plunged into the mountain about
55 miles southeast of the U.S. Iwakuni Marine Air Station. The pilot
bailed out safely, according to marine Sgt. Rick Ecker.
   The pilot was identified as Maj. Robert E. Schmiddle Jr. His
hometown was not immediately available.
   A rescue helicopter from the Iwakuni base picked up Schmiddle
about 50 minutes after the crash, and he was taken to a clinic for a
checkup.
   The cause of the crash was under investigation.
</TEXT>
