<HEAD>Educators To Hold AIDS Education Home Parties</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   County health educators are modeling an AIDS
education program on parties used to sell housewares or lingerie.
   ``A hostess will invite up to 15 acquaintances and maybe serve
refreshments,'' said Alice K. Stambaugh, education coordinator for
the Maricopa County Health Department. ``It's a more intimate
setting. People can be more open and ask questions they normally
would not ask.''
   At the parties, bilingual county representatives will discuss
