<HEAD>Typhoon Dot Blasts Northern Vietnam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Typhoon Dot blasted coastal provinces of
northern Vietnam with winds gusting up to 72 mph, the Vietnam News
agency reported Monday.
   Torrential rains fell on large regions of the Red River Delta on
Sunday and many parts of the capital of Hanoi were flooded by up to
three feet of water, the report said.
   The typhoon also hit the coastal town of Haiphong and submerged
rice fields about to be harvested in the provinces of Thai Binh, Ha
Nam Ninh, Hai Hung and Ha Bac, the news agency said.
   At the end of May, tropical storm Cecil swept through central
Vietnam, devastating a wide area and killing 78 people.
