<TEXT>
   Calling herself ``strictly an amateur,'' Imelda
Marcos has released her first album _ a collection of her ailing
husband's favorite love songs sung by her and Philippine pop star
Imelda Papin.
   ``We're working on a music video and that should be out soon,''
said Ms. Papin.
   The former Philippine first lady sang for votes for 20 years in
her homeland but is hoping to reach another audience with her first
stab at commercial success.
   ``It's nice to be recognized for something positive, something
beautiful, like music,'' she said Sunday before a reception
heralding the release of ``Imelda Papin Featuring Songs with Mrs.
Imelda Romualdez Marcos.''
   Mrs. Marcos, 59, said she agreed to join Ms. Papin, who has 25
gold or platinum albums in her homeland, after recording some songs
as a gift to her husband, Ferdinand, on their 35th wedding
anniversary May 1.
   Mrs. Marcos said her singing perked up her critically ill
husband. Marcos, 71, has been hospitalized since January.
