<HEAD>China Makes Additional Grain Purchase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China has purchased another 100,000 metric tons
of U.S. wheat for delivery in the 1989-90 marketing year that began
June 1, the Agriculture Department said Monday.
   The latest sale boosted to more than 2.75 million tons the amount
of U.S. wheat that China has purchased for 1989-90 delivery. Last
year's sales totaled 8.3 million tons, making China the leading
foreign market for American wheat farmers.
   A metric ton is about 2,205 pounds and is equal to 36.7 bushels
of wheat.
