<FIRST>r i AM-Iran-Religion     06-12 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Iran-Religion,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Former Teacher of Khomeini named Paramount Religious Leader</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Iran-Khomeini Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former teacher of Ayatollah Ruhollah
Khomeini has been chosen as Iran's paramount religious leader, the
official Islamic Republic News Agency reported Monday.
   It said Ayatollah Mohammad Ali Araki, 95, was selected by
prominent Shiite Moslem theologians to succeed Khomeini who died
June 3 at the age of 86.
   The paramount religious leader, or marja' taqlid, is Iran's
authority on religious matters.
   Khomeini was Iran's highest religious and political authority.
President Ali Khamenei, who succeeded in the political role, is a
middle-ranking cleric without the authority to rule on religious
matters.
   The news agency said Araki has written a Towzih al-Maisal, a book
paramount religious leaders prepare as a guide, but he told
followers to use the book written by Khomeini. Araki taught Khomeini
at the Qom Theological Seminary in Iran.
</TEXT>
