<FIRST>r a AM-BusAccident     06-12 0232</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bus Accident,0238</SECOND>
<HEAD>One Girl Dies, Nine Injured in Bus Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A private school bus taking students home from
their first day in summer school collided with a truck Monday,
killing one girl and injuring nine others.
   The bus was carrying seventh- and eighth-grade girls attending
summer classes at the Chinquapin School, a private preparatory
school in the small community of Highlands, school secretary Debra
Hicks said.
   One girl was killed in the accident at an intersection at about
4:30 p.m., but Ms. Hicks did not know her age.
   Emergency medical service officials said the injured _ nine
students and three adults _ were transferred to several area
hospitals. The drivers of the school bus, the truck and a motorcycle
also were hospitalized.
   Three girls were in stable condition at San Jacinto Methodist
Hospital in nearby Baytown, hospital spokeswoman Jeanni Pruitt said.
Two other girls taken to Sunbelt Regional Medical Center did not
have serious injuries, a hospital official said.
   Three girls were taken to Doctors Hospital-East Loop, but
hospital officials could not release any information about their
conditions.
   Three adults and one student were taken to Hermann Hospital. Two
of the adults and the girl were in stable condition, and one adult
was in guarded condition, hospital spokeswoman Katherine Byard said.
   Harris County Sheriff's officials did not have any immediate
details about what caused the multi-vehicle accident.
</TEXT>
