<DOCNO> AP890612-0184 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-12-89 2248EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-GoldenPen     06-12 0283</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Golden Pen,0290</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviet Publisher Wins Freedom Award</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LINDA ASHTON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sergei Grigoryants, a Soviet magazine
publisher once imprisoned as a dissident, received the International
Federation of Newspaper Publishers 1989 ``Golden Pen of Freedom''
award on Monday.
   ``A few years ago the Golden Pen of Freedom had no place in the
USSR'' and countless other places, Grigoryants said, speaking
through an interpreter.
   ``Today we see the great dragon being defeated not only by the
force of the spear, but also by the healing injection of the free
word,'' he told about 300 at the World Congress of Newspaper
Publishers.
   Grigoryants, 48, founded the independent Soviet magazine
``Glasnost'' in 1987. He began publication soon after his release
from a Soviet labor camp where he had been imprisoned in 1983 for
publishing ``Bulletin V,'' an underground newspaper on human rights.
   Since starting ``Glasnost,'' Grigoryants has been harassed and
his editing and publishing equipment destroyed for writing stories
about the KGB, immigration rules and the destruction of judicial
archives, said Professor Lord McGregor of Durris, England, and
chairman of the committee that searches for Golden Pen honorees.
   Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev has described ``Glasnost'' as
a ``parasite funded by the West,'' McGregor said.
   Grigoryants responded, ``A really free press is not popular with
anyone in power, not only in the Soviet Union but in the West, too.''
   The Golden Pen award was created in 1961 to recognize the
oustanding actions of an individual, group or institution in favor
of freedom of the press. In 1988, the award was given posthumously
to Naji El-Ali, a Lebanese cartoonist.
   The World Congress of Newspaper Publishers continues through
Wednesday in New Orleans.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP890612-0185 </DOCNO>
