<TEXT>
   You want your kid to love the world? Let him cuddle a soft,
stuffed world globe called Hugg-a-Planet Earth.
   The basic soft sculpture Earth measures 12 inches in diameter and
maps out political boundaries, continents, countries, oceans,
islands, states and provinces in bright primary colors.
   Robert Forenza, the manufacturer, says the idea is to encourage
people ``to develop a natural curiosity about the planet and to
appreciate its natural beauty.''
   Also in the product line are 6- and 24-inch versions, a
geographic version with natural physical features, globes featuring
constellations (one with the path of Halley's Comet), and the Peace
Bear, a white teddy bear with a baby planet. Soft-sculptured Mars
and United States maps will be added this year.
