<FIRST>d f BC-Swiss-Ivory     06-12 0122</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Swiss-Ivory,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Swiss Ban Ivory Imports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Switzerland has become the latest
European country to ban all imports of ivory.
   The Swiss measure, which takes effect Tuesday, closes freeport
warehouses to ivory shipments and forbids re-export from
Switzerland, an economics ministry announcement said.
   Environment ministers of the 12-nation European Community last
Friday called on all members to bar ivory imports, a response to
growing concern about the rapid decimation of African elephant
herds, much of it by poachers.
   France, West Germany and Denmark had banned ivory imports earlier.
   Switzerland, which is not an EC member but borders on three,
bought less than 0.1 percent of African raw ivory exports totaling
115 tons last year, according to official statistics.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
