<FIRST>u f AM-OilPrices     06-12 0166</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gasoline Futures Prices Drop on Technical Factors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gasoline futures prices tumbled on largely
technical factors Monday, carrying crude and home heating oil
futures along the way.
   Wholesale unleaded gasoline for July delivery fell 1.99 cents a
gallon to 61.73 cents on the New York Mercantile Exchange.
   Peter Beutel, assistant director of the energy group at Elders
Futures Inc., said the gasoline market traded down as investors with
long positions sold off some holdings.
   ``The market continued to move lower and developed a momentum of
its own'' after falling through the 47 cents level, Beutel said.
   Meanwhile, the July contract for West Texas Intermediate, the
benchmark grade of U.S. crude oil, dropped 62 cents to $19.26 a
gallon on the heels of the gasoline decline.
   Beutel described Monday's trading as ``the gas and the crude
working hand and glove.''
   Home heating oil, brought lower by technical and seasonal
factors, slumped 1.58 cents a gallon to settle at 45.45 cents.
</TEXT>
